<subSubSection id="99A324856CE6E8D01FE0CFEBAAC54F55" pageId="null" pageNumber="150" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph id="CC921244AEA8BB34250D1CD11FF217A3" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">Kurzstenglige Gemskresse</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="095604E3F77B72CBA099660B4EF672DB" pageId="null" pageNumber="150" type="description">
<paragraph id="5DFFC0CD5191FCC7105ED4D9D12A8C45" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">
Unterscheidet sich von 
<taxonomicName id="6D0EC7A73323157A3E90959118B4C5F4" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Noccaea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="null" pageNumber="150" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alpina">
<emphasis id="0595E6695E8057BA16159D58E71F272F" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">H. alpina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 2) durch folgende Merkmale: 2-5 cm hoch; seitliche Blattabschnitte 1- 
<normalizedToken id="E52938A68988DEF1A7128F7C700B5C9C" originalValue="1½" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">11/2</normalizedToken>
mal so lang wie breit; 
<normalizedToken id="8A35937D0C52BA16C2E739066966F980" originalValue="Blütenstand" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">Bluetenstand</normalizedToken>
nach der 
<normalizedToken id="68AE74D453FC41FB763CA72B5BBC81A5" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">Bluete</normalizedToken>
kaum 
<normalizedToken id="6647C5A7BBD1819D2ED9F3B27E7A63BA" originalValue="verlängert" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">verlaengert</normalizedToken>
; 
<emphasis id="3E8AF8B4BC4E43798A51808B4D3D743D" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">
<normalizedToken id="529050BF14B30303A1DB8219CC8AA942" originalValue="Kronblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">Kronblaetter</normalizedToken>
2,5-4 mm lang und 1-2 mm breit, 
<normalizedToken id="7333642AB12AF5C126CD65EB2587CFB0" originalValue="allmählich" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">allmaehlich</normalizedToken>
in den stielartigen untern Teil 
<normalizedToken id="67EF45BA94A69BB3CA92D9F3D98FB2B0" originalValue="verschmälert" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">verschmaelert</normalizedToken>
; 
<normalizedToken id="4FCF14A9FB12CAFF3C26F6704FBCB67E" originalValue="Früchte" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">Fruechte</normalizedToken>
3,5-4 mm lang
</emphasis>
, ca. 2mal so lang wie breit; 
<emphasis id="7D1F186F3D6EF7117C545315E7C037D8" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">Griffel 0,1-0,2 mm lang; Samen 1,2-1,5 mm lang.</emphasis>
- 
<normalizedToken id="17C2F6D6BEEA879F694B9E2F0EA319A4" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: Sommer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A55C05484F237048295BA2C10B4ECAA2" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">
<emphasis id="91B7307BFB18DDB98BCB88ED59ECB535" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">Zytologische Angaben. 2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="F50C77CA3B72B9938E2E821376837B9E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">12:</emphasis>
Material aus Tirol (Mattick in Tischler 1950).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="211F83F2CC37FA7DF3B40080E85D9B30" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">
<emphasis id="F150730B3F023212433910983924115D" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">Standort.</emphasis>
Subalpin und alpin. Wie 
<taxonomicName id="75188DE0865F8EAA902E67D443BB659D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Noccaea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="null" pageNumber="150" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alpina">
<emphasis id="4F8C3D0A4DE1931E29994402F0380B93" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">H. alpina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 2), aber auf 
<normalizedToken id="11DA3E68F0031B06A9BB4396039B68EF" originalValue="Silikatschuttböden" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">Silikatschuttboeden</normalizedToken>
. 
<normalizedToken id="E9EACDE9400ADE22E823F6082315EAF7" originalValue="Moränen" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">Moraenen</normalizedToken>
, Feinschutt. 
<emphasis id="39872EB02B5C89D7FF3C01848BFC7FA9" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">Arabidetum coeruleae</emphasis>
Br.-Bl. 1918, 
<emphasis id="0DC3C40C6B04B3FBED9961664AC976EB" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">Oxyrietum digynae</emphasis>
(
<normalizedToken id="F978B3D61B715E635A986F5AECB64841" originalValue="Lüdi" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">Luedi</normalizedToken>
) Br.-Bl. 1926.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="890EDE1D158A7ED7AD111EFEC0D6F9E5" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">
<emphasis id="60FFD04451AE0375F22A126EBEC2EE55" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">
<pageBreakToken id="1BB13BF1724E179B0998F421123DADA1" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">Verbreitung</pageBreakToken>
. Mittel- und 
<normalizedToken id="2699646BD11001E42BD1D0E61C52D815" originalValue="südeuropäische" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">suedeuropaeische</normalizedToken>
Gebirgspflanze
</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="31D3E7550ED1CFCE260102FE73E6D00D" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">
<normalizedToken id="40933FDC33E2281D96C19D9810BCD0FB" originalValue="östlich" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">oestlich</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
): Alpen, Gebirge der Balkanhalbinsel (Bosnien, Montenegro, Albanien), 
<normalizedToken id="0C1C65BEE34C09060DEC2E2F55531A07" originalValue="Südkarpaten" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">Suedkarpaten</normalizedToken>
; die Angaben aus den 
<normalizedToken id="3629F3CE0113EBB63103178B1D3B8AC2" originalValue="Pyrenäen" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">Pyrenaeen</normalizedToken>
sind zu 
<normalizedToken id="BAEA53D870ACC2D7ED02C06C4EAC90D3" originalValue="überprüfen" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">ueberpruefen</normalizedToken>
. - Im Gebiet: Zentralund 
<normalizedToken id="2E1187FF3E228DFF4DA54E1CAF888DA3" originalValue="Südalpen" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">Suedalpen</normalizedToken>
; verbreitet, ziemlich 
<normalizedToken id="917B4C0199A7C84DC962A968E71CEB5B" originalValue="häufig" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">haeufig</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FF8272FF8A8FCC98B0AB1ACCA73CF0D4" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">
<emphasis id="F60898A323DE65E3F642E0C8F08A0432" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">Bemerkungen.</emphasis>
Siehe bei 
<taxonomicName id="CAAC76DC51F72711B5A1C1AA47157452" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Noccaea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="null" pageNumber="150" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alpina">
<emphasis id="B3DC73720E1AD100B3C8C04775971157" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="150">H. alpina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 2).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
